    • getIntegerAsBigInteger

      public BigInteger getIntegerAsBigInteger() throws IOException
      Get CBOR integer as a BigInteger value.

      This method requires that the object is a CBORInteger, otherwise an exception will be thrown.

      This method supports the full (65-bit) CBOR integer range.
      Returns:
      BigInteger
      Throws:
      IOException

    • getLong

      public long getLong() throws IOException
      Get long value.

      This method requires that the object is a CBORInteger and fits a Java (signed) long, otherwise an exception will be thrown.

      Also see getIntegerAsBigInteger().
      Returns:
      Long
      Throws:
      IOException

    • getUnsignedLong

      public long getUnsignedLong() throws IOException
      Get unsigned long value.

      This method requires that the object is a positive CBORInteger and fits a Java long (sign bit is used as well), otherwise an exception will be thrown.

      Also see getIntegerAsBigInteger().
      Returns:
      Long
